# Bottom-up approach
this is like a combination problem
It is given you can can either climb `1` or `2` steps
Meaning, if you are at stair number `i`, from here you can only jump to stair `i+1` or stair `i+2`, now like this you can have multiple ways to reach your target stair.

So, consider these stairs as different levels of a game.
See this picture, to reach round 1, you have two ways, like this at every point, you have two ways to reach the next round
If your final round is `3`,total number of possible paths would be 5.

Intuition: `total ways to reach from i to n` = `total ways to reach from i+1 to n` + `total ways to reach from i+2 to n`

Also, `use an array to store already calculated paths, to save time`.--> important!

```
class Solution {
    int x = 0;
    int[] data = new int[46];
    public int climbStairs(int n) {
        x = n;
        return util(0);
    }
    private int util(int n) {
        if(n == x) {
            return 1;
        }
        if(n > x) {
            return 0;
        }
        if(data[n] == 0) {
            data[n] = util(n+1) + util(n+2);
        }
        return data[n];
    }
}
```

