<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
List the all possible ways for the step from 1 to 6;

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We can see that for the step 1 stair --one way;the step 2 stairs, there are 2ways;step 3, 3ways; step 4, 5ways; step 5, 8ways; and step 6, 13ways.

What do u find?

1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13......

It is the Fibonacci sequence!
And , the answer is easy...


The first attempt i use recursive, unfortunately, it waste a lot of time!!

We only need 3 ints, which are first, second, and third.
And just use the nature of Fibonacci, the third number equals the sum of the first and the second number. 

