int rand10() { 
    // first call map 1-3 to 1 and 4-6 to 0
    int first = rand7();
    int second = rand7();
    while(first > 6 || second > 5){
        first = rand7();
        second = rand7();
    }
    unsigned multiplier = first < 4 ? 0 : 1;
    return second + multiplier*5;
}
```
The idea is that we get a number 1-5 by using a call to rand7() and rejecting 6 and 7. The we use another call to rand7() to get 1-6, rejecting 7, which we can then group into two groups 1-3 and 4-6. If the second number is in the 4-6 range then we add 5 to our first 1-5 that we got, otherwise we don't.

